  "texts": [
    "IC 50) or their binding affinities to a kinase (dissociation constant, such as K i and K d).",
    "Notably, such measurement methods typically do not extend to the ability of a compound to inhibit the entire kinome.",
    "High-throughput kinase profiling assay has also become feasible in recent years, but the excessive cost makes it difficult to use as a routine early stage of drug discovery efforts [12].Based on experimental data, a number of computational methods have been developed and published elsewhere, aiming to significantly reduce the cost, time and laborious involved in experimental identification.",
    "Generally, these computational methods can be classified into two major categories: structure-and ligand-based kinase inhibition and/or profiling prediction approaches (called virtual assay).",
    "Molecular docking, commonly used in structure-based prediction methods for kinase inhibition, has good generalizability, but its accuracy depends on the crystal structure of the kinase and the accuracy of the scoring function [13,14]."
  ]
}